Figure 1 illustrates how our traditional approach to patient education differs from health coaching. Figure 1. Traditional approach vs health coaching. The Patient as the Center Effective chronic illness care requires 2 things: 1. Active involved patient and caregiver 2. Healthcare team that centers on the patient and caregiver. It is estimated that 95% to 99% of chronic illness care is provided by the person who has the illness (Funnell, 2000). This makes sense.
